Iuppiter Anxurus: Anxur, figured as a young beardless man, was the chief male deity of Anxur, a Volscian town, later called Terracina. He was identified with Juppiter.

800. Feronia: a female deity corresponding to Anxur, and identified with Juno Virgo. She was goddess of sprIng, streams, and sacred groves. (Benoist.) In viii. 563—7 we hear of her son Erulus slain by Evander in spite of the three lives that his mother gave him.

801. saturae: not identified, but part of the Pontine marshes.

802. Ufens: here the river which helps to make the Pontine marshes. In 1. 745 a hero.
